    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Euploca dichotoma are euploca infusion, euploca tincture, euploca decoction, euploca salve, and tea. Euploca infusion is made by steeping dried flowers, leaves, or stems in hot water to extract bioactive compounds for treating fever, sore throat, and respiratory issues. Euploca tincture is a concentrated liquid solution of the plant's bioactive compounds extracted using a solvent, commonly used for treating anxiety, insomnia, and digestive problems. Euploca decoction is a boiling method of extraction used to make a stronger concoction than infusion, used for its expectorant properties and treating cough, bronchitis, and asthma. Euploca salve is a topical preparation made by infusing the plant in oil, used for its anti-inflammatory and antiseptic properties to treat wounds, burns, and skin irritations.",
